### Why it looks like this right now:
The browser is successfully reading the text from your `App.jsx`, but because it isn't being "built" by Vite, the Tailwind classes (like `bg-[#0a0a0a]` or `grid-cols-12`) are just ignored. Moving everything into the `src` folder allows Vite to process the CSS and turn those plain words into the professional dashboard design we want.

Once you move those files into the `src` folder and commit the changes, Render will restart the build, and the blue accents, grid layout, and icons should appear.

How are the file moves going on GitHub?
